OL,3,CPoliticians back plans that could give
OL,4,Call prisoners a right to vote
OL,6,FThe step would likely be welcomed by
OL,7,Fthe European Court of Human Rights,
OL,8,Fwhich previously concluded that the
OL,9,FUK's approach to block prisoners from
OL,10,Fvoting is "indiscriminate and
OL,11,Fdisproportionate".
OL,13,FSince those comments in 2005, the UK
OL,14,Fnow lets those on remand and awaiting
OL,15,Fsentencing the right to vote.
OL,17,FMeanwhile, the other Crown
OL,18,FDependencies - Guernsey and the Isle
OL,19,Fof Man - already allow all prisoners
OL,20,Fto have their say in elections.
